Patch Set 1:

Does this really require a release note?  The history of the Artifacts API is:

* Liberty: EXPERIMENTAL v3 on Glance endpoint, code in Glance repo
* Mitaka: EXPERIMENTAL v0.1 on its own endpoint, code in Glance repo
* Newton: EXPERIMENTAL v1.0 on its own endpoint, code in Glare repo

The code we're removing hasn't been used since Mitaka, and hasn't been available on the Glance endpoint since Liberty.  What would the release note say?  I see this patch as pure technical debt payoff.
Uploaded patch set 2.

Patch Set 2:

Missed the semver stuff in glance/common.  Removing it because if we add versioning to images, we should use a standard library.  Alex had some particular reasons why he had to do a roll-your-own semver for artifacts, but I don't think we need the complexity for images.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

So I agree with Nikhil about a Release Note. I'm also not a fan of sneaking this into RC-1. So here's what I propose

1. Add a release note that details the removal of 'glare-*' comands and the complete move of the service to a new project
2. Wait until RC-1 is tagged this week, then merge this.

Patch Set 2: Workflow-1

I agree with Ian.  We'll do this in Pike, right after the Ocata branch is cut later this week.
